RACE.RACE_TEXT: LAUREL PARK RACE 6 1 1/16M Turf CR: 68. Maiden Claiming Purse 31910. (PLUS UP TO 15% MBF) FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000, if for $16,000, allowed 4 lbs. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race on the Turf course, it will be run o n the main track at One Mile) (Rail at 35 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOOD KNIGHT NILE , in range of the dueling leaders while off the inside, was put to a hustling ride leaving the three eighths, shifted out some and advanced into the lane, altered back in to bid between runners in mid stretch, moved to a slim advantage to the inside of STORMING CHROME leaving the sixteenth pole, dueled and held resolutely to the wire. STORMING CHROME , under a firm hold off the leaders into the first turn, steadied along then angled out to be in the clear tracking three wide, bid three deep near the five sixteenths, gained a short lead past the three sixteenths, battled outside the winner through the final furlong and just missed in a sharp effort. CRIPPLE CREEK , taken back soon after the start, dropped in and settled, gained along the rail into the far turn, eased out, circled four wide and ranged up to loom boldly past the three sixteenths but failed to seriously sustain. HUNTINGTON got into a duel to the inside of OBOY soon after the start, carried that battled through backstretch and around the final turn, stayed on as STORMING CHROME joined the fray past the three eighths, drifted out while battling past the three sixteenths, drifted back in and impeded SOLOMON'S CHOICE near the furlong grounds, corrected and gave way grudgingly. WILL'S MUSIC settled off the pace while saving ground, gained some near the rail in mid stretch then flattened out. SOLOMON'S CHOICE saved ground under rating, took closer order past the five sixteenths, checked sharply when attempting to make a run in mid stretch then failed to seriously recover. OBOY dueled outside HUNTINGTON, stayed on between runners heading to the quarter pole, failed to kick on in upper stretch and faltered. Following an objection by the rider of SOLOMON'S CHOICE, HUNTINGTON was disqualified and placed sixth for causing interference in mid stretch. An objection by the rider of SOLOMON'S CHOICE against the winner for alleged interference in mid stretch was not allowed.
